      "agentSubtype": "success",
      "agentResultText": "\n\nThis is already implemented. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts:19-27` checks for a session on `/dashboard` and `/settings` routes and redirects unauthenticated users to `/auth/login`:\n\n```typescript\nconst isProtected = pathname.startsWith(\"/dashboard\") || pathname.startsWith(\"/settings\");\n\nif (isProtected) {\n  const session = await auth0.getSession(req);\n  if (!session) {\n    const loginUrl = new URL(\"/auth/login\", req.nextUrl.origin);\n    loginUrl.searchParams.set(\"returnTo\", pathname);\n    return NextResponse.redirect(loginUrl);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAdditionally, the server-side `getCurrentUser()` helper in `src/lib/auth.ts` calls `redirect(\"/auth/login\")` if there's no session — so even if middleware is bypassed, the pages and server actions themselves enforce authentication.\n\nThe nav in `src/app/layout.tsx` also conditionally hides Dashboard/Settings links for unauthenticated users.",
